gomodel:SYNGO_1640  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The supplemental table S1 contains proteins identified in the PSD preparation (Synaptic junctional protein preparation).\nFor proteins coming from datasets derived from PSD (detergent-resistant synaptic junctions) preparations without defined selection / enrichment of the pre- or postsynaptic compartment we cannot assign these proteins to excitatory and/or inhibitory nor to the presynapse or / and postsynapse without further information.\n\n13/10/2017 Pim\n- listed as 40S ribosomal protein S23 in Table S1. Experimental description: Briefly adult mouse brains (2-16 months, 20 animals, 10 g wet weight) were homogenized ... p. 915" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
